a drive system configured to generate a low actuation rate rotary motion during a first operating mode and a high actuation rate rotary motion during a second operating mode;
a control system configured to switch between said first operating mode and said second operating mode;
a user interface configured to allow a user to selectively switch between said first operating mode and said second operating mode;
a drive member;
a locking system which prevents the advancement of said drive member if said unspent staple cartridge is not correctly seated in said end effector; and
a rotatable member operably coupled with said drive system, wherein said rotatable member is in operable engagement with said drive member, wherein said low actuation rate rotary motion from said drive system moves said drive member at a first rate, and wherein said high actuation rate rotary motion from said drive system moves said drive member at a second rate.
3. A surgical stapling system, comprising:
a shaft;
an end effector, comprising:
a first jaw; and
a second jaw movable relative to said first jaw between an open position and a clamped position;
an unspent staple cartridge comprising staples removably stored therein;
an articulation joint disposed proximal to said end effector, wherein said end effector is rotatable relative to said shaft about said articulation joint;
